      "_template": "faqAccordion",
      "heading": "Professional Resources FAQs",
      "faqs": [
        {
          "question": "Can I download all these resources at once?",
          "answer": "You can download individual guides via the tabs above. For a complete package of all professional resources, email professionals@psychologydirect.co.uk. We'll send a ZIP file."
        },
        {
          "question": "Who has written these guides?",
          "answer": "All guides are written by experienced independent practitioners and senior clinicians with 15+ years' experience in private practice."
        },
        {
          "question": "Are these resources updated regularly?",
          "answer": "Yes. We update guides annually and immediately when regulations change, including Legal Aid rates, GDPR updates, and HCPC requirements. Subscribe to our professional newsletter to get notified."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can I share these resources with colleagues?",
          "answer": "Yes. Share freely with colleagues in your professional network. We ask that you credit Psychology Direct, but we don't require permission."
        },
        {
          "question": "I'm interested in joining Psychology Direct. Where do I start?",
          "answer": "Visit /about/careers/ for application information. Or email professionals@psychologydirect.co.uk. We'll send you a joining information pack."
        },
        {
          "question": "What are the current Legal Aid rates?",
          "answer": "See the Legal Aid Rates Summary in the Fees tab. Rates are updated annually. Subscribe to our newsletter for updates."
        },
        {
          "question": "I need guidance on a specific professional topic not listed. Can you help?",
          "answer": "Email professionals@psychologydirect.co.uk with your question. We create resources based on practitioner needs and may add it to the library."
        },
        {
          "question": "Are these resources suitable for psychologists and psychiatrists?",
          "answer": "Most resources apply to both disciplines. Some sections are discipline-specific, for example psychology report templates differ from psychiatry ones. Check the relevant tabs."
        }
      ]
    },
